    Is Kill movie a hit or flop?
    Can't generate an AI overview right now. Try again later.An AI Overview is not available for this search
    AI Overview
    The movie "Kill" can be considered a box office success, as it made more money than its production budget. The film grossed 47.12 crore worldwide, exceeding its 40 crore budget. It also received generally favorable reviews from critics. 
    Here's a more detailed breakdown: 
    • Budget: 40 crore.
    • Worldwide Gross: 47.12 crore.
    • India Gross: 28.75 crore.
    • Overseas Gross: 18.37 crore.
    • Critical Reception: Generally positive, with Rotten Tomatoes giving it a 7.2/10 rating and Metacritic rating it 74 out of 100.

        What is Kill 9 and Kill 15?
        (signal 15) is a request to the program to terminate. If the program has a signal handler for SIGTERM that does not actually terminate the application, this kill may have no effect. This is the default signal sent by kill. (signal 9) is a directive to kill the process immediately.
